01/03/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Former Bulgarian Prime Minister and the former leader of the opposition Union of Democratic Forces Ivan Kostov has officially initiated a procedure for registering a new rightist party. 
He says the new party will likely become functional in May.
In other news, Bulgarian Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Economy Lidia Shouleva kicks off an official six-day visit to the United States on Monday (1 March). 
Shouleva is heading a delegation that includes representatives of 17 leading Bulgarian companies in the IT, defence and auto industries. 
(BTA, News.bg - 29/02/04; BTA, Mediapool- 28/02/04)
